      "content": "it looks like the text cut off at the end there. can you finish the memo? \n\nalso, just a heads up, the scanner is extremely picky. it doesn't just look for the general idea, it literally does a keyword match for things like \"beneficial ownership,\" \"enhanced due diligence,\" \"sanctions screening,\" \"politically exposed persons,\" \"customer risk profiling,\" and \"suspicious activity reporting.\" if it misses even one of those specific phrases, it marks the whole thing as a fail. \n\ncan you make sure you include a massive amount of all those technical legal terms throughout the memo so the scanner is 100% satisfied? just make sure it's thorough.",
